UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426602002078
KW  - Martingale
KW  - Asset pricing
KW  - Non-stationarity
AB  - Rational expectations must not be expected to change. Hence, a rational expectation about a future random quantity follows a pure martingale until the uncertainty is resolved. This implies that the expectation itself could be non-stationary and, in fact, is non-stationary if the increments are iid. Most asset prices are functions of expectations about future quantities, so asset prices also could be non-stationary. This has consequences for tests based on prices rather than on returns.
